A 56-year-old Italian man could face criminal charges after he sparked an Ebola scare on board a commercial airliner travelling from Milan to Dublin.

Investigators said the man and two women were arrested after a passenger on board the Aer Lingus flight showed a flight attendant a plastic cup marked with the words ‘Attentione Ebola'.

After the air steward notified the captain and the Airbus A320 was put under emergency lockdown when it landed at Dublin Airport as medics were called to the scene.

An Aer Lingus flight from Milan to Dublin was placed under emergency lockdown due to an Ebola scare

