Three passengers were arrested and questioned under provisions of the Air Navigation and Transport Act.

Gardai said the 56-year-old man is scheduled to appear in court on Friday while the two women, aged 23 and 51, were released without charge.

Thursday’s incident is the latest scare to occur aboard an aircraft as airports around the world screen passengers for the deadly Ebola virus.

